snippet.textDisplay:
HISTORY OF THE FROG PIT
The second of the short stories to reflect on tells us about the power of other people's opinions. He says there was a large group of frogs that was always going to have fun in the woods. They all sang and jumped until night fell. They remained dead with laughter and nothing separated them. One day, on their usual departure, they went to see a new forest. They were in their games when three of them fell into a deep ditch that none of them had noticed. The rest were shocked. They looked at the bottom of the moat and saw that it was too deep. "We lost them," they said.The three fallen frogs tried to climb the walls of the moat, but it was very difficult. They were barely a meter ahead and fell again. The others began to comment that their efforts were futile. How could they manage to climb such a high wall? It was better that they resign themselves. There was nothing to do. Two of the frogs heard those comments and began to surrender. They thought the others were right. The third frog, on the other hand, kept rising and falling, but after a couple of hours, it managed to surface. The others were amazed. One asked, "How did you do it?" But the frog did not answer. She was deaf.
